<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN304-intro">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. aricilkiḻār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN304">
<l>koṭuṅkuḻai makaḷir kōtai cūṭi</l>
<l>naṭuṅkupaṉik kaḷaiiyar nārari paruki</l>
<l>vaḷitoḻi loḻikkum vaṇparip puravi</l>
<l>paṇṇaṟku viraiti nīyē nerunai</l>
<l>yemmuṟ  ṟappiyōṉ  ṟampiyo ṭorāṅku</l>
<l>nāḷaic ceykuve ṉamareṉak kūṟip</l>
<l>puṉvayi ṟaruttaluñ cellāṉ paṉmāṇ</l>
<l>kaṭavu meṉpa peritē yatukēṭṭu</l>
<l>valampaṭu muraciṉ velpōr vēnta</l>
<l>ṉilaṅkirum pācaṟai naṭuṅkiṉ</l>
<l>ṟiraṇṭā kātavaṉ kūṟiya teṉavē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l>“You, you should make haste</l>
<l>to put on a garland [given by] girls with curved earrings,</l>
<l>drink [toddy] that is filtered through fibres in order to remove the shivering fever,</l>
<l>[and] prepare a horse of generous motion that outruns the wind. Yesterday</l>
<l>my elder brother failed, [and] tomorrow I shall make war</l>
<l>just like that with [his] younger brother,” saying so,</l>
<l>he could not even feed [his] puny stomach, he strongly</l>
<l>urged many times, they say. Having heard that,</l>
<l>the shining large army camp of the king of victorious war </l>
<l>with a victory-bringing drum trembled</l>
<l>in the thought that what he said [and what he would do] would not be two things.  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
